delta U prime [? c ?]

00:54:02.870 --> 00:54:04.040
times 1 plus r.

00:54:04.040 --> 00:54:08.080
So basically, I'm getting more
utility by putting money into

00:54:08.080 --> 00:54:09.330
the future.

00:54:13.650 --> 00:54:15.920
So that's the standard condition
for consumption

00:54:15.920 --> 00:54:17.170
optimality.

00:54:19.620 --> 00:54:22.560
The next line says, imagine the
utility function that's a

00:54:22.560 --> 00:54:26.460
